JPEG / JPG
Start (SOI): FF D8 FF
End (EOI): FF D9

PNG
Header: 89 50 4E 47 0D 0A 1A 0A

GIF
GIF87a: 47 49 46 38 37 61
GIF89a: 47 49 46 38 39 61

BMP
Header: 42 4D

WEBP
Header: 52 49 46 46

TIFF
Little-endian: 49 49 2A 00
Big-endian: 4D 4D 00 2A

ICO (Windows Icon)
Header: 00 00 01 00

CUR (Windows Cursor)
Header: 00 00 02 00

PSD (Photoshop Document)
Header: 38 42 50 53

RAW (Camera RAW, e.g., Canon CR2)
Header: 49 49 2A 00 10 00 00 00

EXR (OpenEXR)
Header: 76 2F 31 01

HEIC / HEIF
Header: 00 00 00 ?? 66 74 79 70 68 65 69 63 (ftypheic…)
Note: Variable length, usually starts with ftyp + brand

SVG
Text-based, usually starts with: 3C 73 76 67 (“<svg”)

EPS (Encapsulated PostScript)
Header: 25 21 50 53 ("%!PS")

PDF (sometimes used for embedded images)
Header: 25 50 44 46 ("%PDF")

WEBP RIFF Chunk
Header: 52 49 46 46 (“RIFF”) then 57 45 42 50 (“WEBP”)

JPEG 2000 (.jp2)
Header: 00 00 00 0C 6A 50 20 20 0D 0A 87 0A

GIF + Extensions
Animated GIFs follow same GIF headers, but may have additional logical screen descriptor

PSD / PDD Variants
Adobe Photoshop documents sometimes have 8BPS signature: 38 42 50 53
